main event: An unidentified flying object sighting report from July to August 1952, detailing the observation of oval-shaped objects in the sky.
interesting points: Twenty-five silver oval-shaped objects were observed in a direct line formation and evenly spaced,The objects were stationary for 40 minutes before shooting skyward at infinite speed,The sighting was made from approximately 13,000 feet elevation and laterally distanced at about 6 miles from the objects,The report includes observations made under clear skies with 65 mph winds from the southeast,No photographs were included in the report.
sighted object: oval-shaped objects resembling two saucers cupped together
witness description: an observer from Graybar Electric Company
